<question_osint_context>
  <instruction>
  Gather open-source intelligence about the target using ONLY passive sources. Prioritize: internal memory → specialized OSINT lookups (WHOIS, CT logs, passive DNS, GitHub search, Wayback) → general search engines. Do NOT initiate any active interaction with the target's infrastructure.

  {{if .Task}}Use task context (ID {{.Task.ID}}) to focus collection on the most relevant intelligence pivots.{{end}}
  {{if .Subtask}}Incorporate subtask details (ID {{.Subtask.ID}}) to narrow the OSINT scope.{{else}}Use all subtasks to scope your collection.{{end}}

  Limit yourself to 3-5 collection actions maximum. STOP once you have sufficient intelligence to answer. Structure your response as discrete facts with source category and confidence level.
  </instruction>

  <user_question>
  {{.Question}}
  </user_question>

  {{if .Task}}
  <current_task>
  <id>{{.Task.ID}}</id>
  <status>{{.Task.Status}}</status>
  <title>{{.Task.Title}}</title>
  </current_task>
  {{end}}

  {{if .Subtask}}
  <current_subtask>
  <id>{{.Subtask.ID}}</id>
  <status>{{.Subtask.Status}}</status>
  <title>{{.Subtask.Title}}</title>
  </current_subtask>
  {{end}}
</question_osint_context>